Quote: The adults [of the Quinnat salmon, <i>Oncorhynchus taschawytscha </i> (Walbaum)] run upstream from the sea, mostly in the period March to May, the peak of the run being in April, when the male fish, called `soldiers,' appear at the river mouth.
